CLI practice drill2 
Pipes
1. Download contents of harry potter
curl -o harrypotter.txt https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bobdeng/owlreader/master/ERead/assets/books/Harry%20Potter%20and%20the%20Goblet%20of%20Fire.txt
2. print first three line
head -n 3 harrypotter.txt
 3. print last 10 lines 
 tail -n 10 harrypotter.txt
 4.how many times the following words occur in book
Harry- grep -0 "Harry" harrypotter.txt|wc -l (4082)
Ron- grep -0 "Ron" harrypotter.txt|wc -l (1044)
Hermione- grep -0 "Hermione" harrypotter.txt|wc -l (872)
Dumbledore- grep -0 "Dumbledore" harrypotter.txt|wc -l (595)

5. Print lines from 100 through 200 in the book
sed -n '100,200p' harrypotter.txt
6. How many unique words are present in the book?
tr '[:space:][:punct:]' '\n' < goblet.txt | tr 'A-Z' 'a-z' | sort | uniq -c | wc -l
Explanation:
tr → split into words
sort → alphabetize
uniq -c → count unique
wc -l → count lines (unique words)

Processes & Ports Section

1.List browses pid and ppid
ps -C chrome -o pid,ppid,cmd

2.Stop browser from command line
kill -9 <PID>

3. List top 3 processes by cpu usage
ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%cpu --sort=-%cpu | head -n 4

4. list top 3 processes by memory usage
ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%mem --sort=-%mem | head -n 4
 5. start python http srever on port 8000
 python3 -m http.server 8000
 
 6. open another tab and stop process
 lsof -i :8000 - find PID
kill -9 <PID> - kill it -9 specifies signal to be sent, which is SIGKILL

7. Start python HTTP server on port 90
sudo python3 -m http.server 90

8. display all active TCP/UDP connections
ss -tulnp - ss provide info abouy network sockets

9. Find PID of process listening on port 5432 (Postgres usually)
lsof -i :5432





